snippet.textDisplay:
Be very very...veeeery careful with statements to the sound quality, they are ALWAYS subjective.
What are the adjustments of the players eq? maybe the headphone internal eq? what player do you use? source file? mp3 128, wma, wav, flac? Does your mobile support aptx hd when you want to play flac via BT?

NEVER buy headphones alone by hearsay. Test them, with your device and you music.

In the case of a kickstarter product, wait till NOT an influencer puts out his/her opinion on YT, check if they get it free or as promo, gather at least 3+ opinions and then decide or gather Information from forums, it should be possible.
Get yourself informed and do some serious recherche.

snippet.textDisplay: Good chance this could have been an impulse buy from me. As I am now looking for a wireless around-the-ear option that rivals the wired headphones (which I currently use for all my gaming, PC, and movie experiences -- I no longer use traditional speakers, at all). But seeing as this is a kickstarter-esc option, that ships in July, I am going to pass and just find some cheap alternative to get me by for my current needs. I needed something for now, not later. Would have been wise to hold off mentioning these until they were being commercially produced and available ASAP. But who knows, the next time I need a nice audiophile set of wireless headphones maybe I'll remember this video and the brand. No way I'll forget the context of the bookmark I made... right?
